cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is about studying the expressive power of a logic fragment (Dependence Logic) and its complexity class capturing ability. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity class P and NP-complete problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with sets decidable in polynomial time. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the expressive power of a logic fragment and its ability to capture complexity classes, which are relevant to AI. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with logic and complexity theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics.
